Steps:-
Part 1: Set Up the Topology and Initialize Devices
Step 1: Connect all routers, switches, and PCs according to the topology.
Step 2: Power on all devices.
Step 3: Erase old configurations (if required).
Router> enable
Router# erase startup-config
Router# reload

Part 2: Configure Devices and Verify Connectivity

Step 1: Configure HTTP Server and Local Authentication (R1)
R1> enable
R1# configure terminal

R1(config)# ip http server
R1(config)# ip http authentication local

R1(config)# username admin privilege 15 secret class

Step 2: Configure SSH Access
R1(config)# ip domain-name cisco.com

R1(config)# crypto key generate rsa
How many bits in the modulus [512]: 1024

R1(config)# line vty 0 4
R1(config-line)# login local
R1(config-line)# transport input ssh
R1(config-line)# exit


Step 3: Configure OSPF Routing
R1(config)# router ospf 1

R1(config-router)# network 192.168.1.0 0.0.0.255 area 0
R1(config-router)# network 10.1.1.0 0.0.0.3 area 0

R1(config-router)# end

Part 3: Configure and Verify Extended Numbered and Named ACLs

Step 1: Configure Numbered Extended ACL (R1)
R1(config)# access-list 100 remark Allow Web and SSH access

R1(config)# access-list 100 permit tcp host 192.168.10.3 host 10.2.2.1 eq 22
R1(config)# access-list 100 permit tcp any any eq 80

R1(config)# interface s0/0/0
R1(config-if)# ip access-group 100 out
R1(config-if)# exit

Step 2: Configure Named Extended ACL on R3
R3(config)# ip access-list extended WEB-POLICY

R3(config-ext-nacl)# permit tcp 192.168.30.0 0.0.0.255 host 10.1.1.1 eq 80
R3(config-ext-nacl)# permit tcp 192.168.30.0 0.0.0.255 209.165.200.224 0.0.0.31 eq 80

R3(config-ext-nacl)# exit

R3(config)# interface s0/0/1
R3(config-if)# ip access-group WEB-POLICY out
R3(config-if)# end




Part 4: Modify and Verify Extended ACLs

Step 1: Modify Numbered ACL
R1(config)# ip access-list extended 100
R1(config-ext-nacl)# permit tcp 192.168.30.0 0.0.0.255 any
R1(config-ext-nacl)# end

Step 2: Modify Named ACL
R3(config)# ip access-list extended WEB-POLICY
R3(config-ext-nacl)# 30 permit tcp 192.168.30.0 0.0.0.255 any
R3(config-ext-nacl)# end

Step 3: Verify Configuration
show ip access-lists
show ip interface
show ip route
show ip ospf neighbor
